    {
      "type": "code",
      "title": "PATTERN: SIMPLE XOR DECODE",
      "language": "text",
      "code": "for i in range(len(buf)):\n    buf[i] ^= key\n\nClue: one byte key, reversible, often used for short strings or configs."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "title": "PATTERN: REPEATING-KEY XOR",
      "language": "text",
      "code": "for i in range(len(buf)):\n    out[i] = buf[i] ^ key[i % key_len]\n\nClue: repeating key schedule, common in toy ciphers and crackmes."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "title": "PATTERN: CRC-LIKE TABLE LOOP",
      "language": "text",
      "code": "crc = table[(crc ^ byte) & 0xFF] ^ (crc >> 8)\n\nClue: 256-entry table, byte-indexed lookup, rolling accumulator."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "title": "PATTERN: DJB2-STYLE HASH",
      "language": "text",
      "code": "hash = 5381\nfor c in data:\n    hash = ((hash << 5) + hash) + c\n\nClue: multiply by 33 using shift+add."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "title": "PATTERN: FNV-1A-STYLE HASH",
      "language": "text",
      "code": "hash ^= byte\nhash *= PRIME\n\nClue: xor then multiply by fixed constant in a byte loop."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "title": "PATTERN: BASE64 ENCODE/DECODE SHAPE",
      "language": "text",
      "code": "Take 3 bytes -> split into 4 groups of 6 bits -> map through alphabet.\nFor decode: reverse-map chars -> combine 6-bit chunks back to bytes.\n\nClue: shifts/masks with 0x3F and alphabet tables."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "title": "PATTERN: TEA-LIKE ROUND SHAPE",
      "language": "text",
      "code": "sum += delta\nv0 += ((v1 << 4) + k0) ^ (v1 + sum) ^ ((v1 >> 5) + k1)\nv1 += ((v0 << 4) + k2) ^ (v0 + sum) ^ ((v0 >> 5) + k3)\n\nClue: shifts, xor, add, two halves, repeated rounds, delta constant."
